Tramp
=====

Tramp is a rails plugin of Martin's Fowler "Accounting Patterns". It include Account, Event, Accounting Entry, Accounting Transaction and Posting Rule.

It includes also a special rule engine allowing user to specify the way accounting must be.




Example
=======

1. Exemple for accounting monetary events

	class MonetaryEvent < ActiveRecord::Base
  
	  include Tramp::Event::InstanceMethods
	  extend Tramp::Event::ClassMethods
  
	  attr_accessor :direct_orders
  
	  rule :monetary_posting_rule

	end
	
	class MonetaryPostingRule < ActiveRecord::Base

	  include Tramp::Rule::InstanceMethods
	  extend Tramp::Rule::ClassMethods

	  movement do |rule|
	    rule.add_collection(:direct_orders)
	  end  

	end


